    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Moscow Embassy Files, Lot F–96</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                        Chairman of the Soviet Council of People’s Commissars</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stalin</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="20" xml:id="d525fn20">Transmitted in a letter from
                        Ambassador Standley to Foreign Commissar Molotov on September 11. The latter
                        acknowledged receipt of the letter in a note dated the same day, and stated
                        that “the message in question has been transmitted by me to its
                        destination”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="21" xml:id="d525fn21">Other portions
                            of this message (which concluded with the statement: “I really feel that
                            the three of us are making real headway.”) are printed on <ref
                                target="#pg_785">p. 785</ref> and in <ref
                                target="frus1943CairoTehran#pg_24">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Conferences at Cairo
                                and Tehran, 1943, p. 24</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-10">September 10,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Regarding the meeting of our three representatives, I will cheerfully agree that
                    the place of meeting be Moscow and the date the beginning of October—say Monday,
                    the fourth. I will send you in two or three days a suggested informal list of
                    subjects to be discussed, but I think the three members should feel free, after
                    becoming acquainted with each other, to discuss any other matters which may come
                    up.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
